    "body": [
      {
        "type": "Heading",
        "level": 1,
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "Text",
            "value": "The Letter by the Culvert"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "Paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "Text",
            "value": "Rain had been falling since breakfast, the kind of rain that made every fence post look older and every road feel longer."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "Paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "Text",
            "value": "Mira, a fox with a satchel full of "
          },
          {
            "type": "Emphasis",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "Text",
                "value": "borrowed library books"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "Text",
            "value": ", cut across the orchard because she was late and because being late felt better than turning back."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "Paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "Text",
            "value": "At the edge of the field she found a letter pinned beneath a stone, the paper gone soft but the ink still "
          },
          {
            "type": "Strong",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "Text",
                "value": "stubborn"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "Text",
            "value": "."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "BlockQuote",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "Paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "Text",
                "value": "If this reaches anyone kind, please carry it to the red house"
              },
              {
                "type": "SoftBreak"
              },
              {
                "type": "Text",
                "value": "beyond the bridge. My father waits there every Thursday."
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "Paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "Text",
            "value": "She looked up at the bridge, then at the river, then at the"
          },
          {
            "type": "SoftBreak"
          },
          {
            "type": "Text",
            "value": "letter again as if it might choose its own owner."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "Paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "Text",
            "value": "In her satchel she had only three useful things:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "List",
        "ordered": false,
        "items": [
          {
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "Paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "Text",
                    "value": "a loaf wrapped in wax paper"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "Paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "Text",
                    "value": "a dry scarf"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "Paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "Text",
                    "value": "a brass key she had never managed to throw away"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "Paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "Text",
            "value": "The bridge planks trembled under her weight, but the river"
          },
          {
            "type": "SoftBreak"
          },
          {
            "type": "Text",
            "value": "below was louder than fear and colder than doubt."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "ThematicBreak"
      },
      {
        "type": "Heading",
        "level": 2,
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "Text",
            "value": "The Red House"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "Paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "Text",
            "value": "The man who opened the door had the careful face of someone"
          },
          {
            "type": "SoftBreak"
          },
          {
            "type": "Text",
            "value": "who had been disappointed often enough to do it politely."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "Paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "Text",
            "value": "Mira held out the letter. For a moment he did not move."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "Paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "Text",
            "value": "Then he laughed once, softly, and pressed a hand to his eyes."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "Paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "Text",
            "value": "\"I wrote this to my brother,\" he said. \"Twenty years ago.\""
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "Paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "Text",
            "value": "They drank tea while the storm walked across the roof."
          },
          {
            "type": "SoftBreak"
          },
          {
            "type": "Text",
            "value": "When Mira left, the rain had thinned to a silver mist,"
          },
          {
            "type": "SoftBreak"
          },
          {
            "type": "Text",
            "value": "and the road home seemed shorter than before."
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
